RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANGELSNDISGUISE pressed the pace down the backstretch while two wide, maintained a steady bid along the rail on the turn, then vied briefly in the early stretch, gained command at the eighth pole and drew clear to prove best in the end. GOLDEN HEIST was away well to set the pressured pace while three wide, clear vied between rivals to keep the lead heading into the lane but was outkicked in late stretch and kept on for second place. CABIN ABBY tracked the pace while four wide, was moving up leaving the turn to battle briefly with inner rivals at the quarter pole, lacked the winning bid and settled for show in the end. ZIINZI raced behind the pack while two wide, bid mildly on the turn then stopped in the stretch. PADDI'S WISH vied for the lead from the inside early, then flattened out throughout the turn and had no final bid in the stretch. CHIRP CHIRP settled behind the field and failed to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BREAKOUT STAR saved ground in the early furlongs along the inside, was advancing in the late backstretch, but found traffic, came out four wide on the far turn, dug in gamely to duel with SMALL SAILOR in the late stretch and kept on well to be up at the wire. SMALL SAILOR stalked the pace while three wide down the backstretch, then took the lead at the top of the far turn, was met with BREAKOUT STAR on the outside to battle grudgingly down the stretch and was out finished in the end. CATEGORY TEN lead the way into the first turn from the inside, then pressed the pace down the early back stretch, dropped back and bumped rival, then settled back on the far turn, rebid in the heading into the stretch, lugged out then found more and finished gamely for the show prize. TOTALITARIAN chased the pace from the inside heading into the first turn, then settled mid pack in the early backstretch, was bumped by a retreating rival around the three eighths marker, regained stride on the far turn, then rallied in the early stretch and just missed the show prize in the end. REITERATION settled behind the pack down the backstretch then bid on the far turn from the two path, angled in towards the rail to avoid rival, and just didn't have enough in the end. MATLOCK settled in the three path down the backstretch, then made a mild bid on the far turn and came up empty in the stretch. TAKE A DIP set the pace down the backstretch while two wide, was in a long drive heading into the far turn, then was overpowered by rivals on both sides and gave way in the stretch. RISKY CHOICE raced in the back group while two wide in the early backstretch, then came three wide heading into the far turn, was moving up to vie gamely for the lead at the quarter pole, was hard used and stopped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 31 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WEST COAST JUSTICE led the way into the first turn, to set the mild pace down the early backstretch, was well rated heading into the far turn, felt the pressure from rivals on both strides, shook clear and drew off heading into the lane, drifted out in late stretch and held sway to prove much the best for Matilda Burnham's first win at Horseshoe Indianapolis. LUSH BE A LADY lead the way briefly from the gate, then pressed the back from the two path down the backstretch, was in a long drive heading into the far turn then flattened out. RED ROSEBUSH was bumped by rival at the start, then settled two to three wide behind the pack down the backstretch, bid on the far turn and was no threat. SUTTON'S PASS chased the pace while three wide down the backstretch, was urging steadily on the far turn then lacked bid in the late stretch.
